OL,3,CRomance scams surge leaving broken
OL,4,Chearts and empty bank accounts
OL,6,FRomance scams are on the rise, with
OL,7,Fvictims losing more money than ever
OL,8,Fbefore as scammers become increasingly
OL,9,Fsophisticated, according to new data.
OL,11,FFigures from TSB reveal that the
OL,12,Famount of money sent to scammers
OL,13,Fjumped by 37%, while the volume of
OL,14,Fcases increased by 15%.
OL,16,FIndustry data revealed that more than
OL,17,F#20.5 million was lost to scammers in
OL,18,Fthe first six months of 2025, across
OL,19,Falmost 3,000 reported cases.
