OL,3,CRomance scams surge leaving broken
OL,4,Chearts and empty bank accounts
OL,6,FOften, stories of financial hardship
OL,7,Fwere used to extract money, accounting
OL,8,Ffor almost half of the cases. More
OL,9,Fthan a third (37%) of victims asked
OL,10,Ffor travel funds, often tied to false
OL,11,Fpromises of meeting in person.
OL,13,FRichard Daniels, TSB's director of
OL,14,Ffraud, said romance scams are among
OL,15,Fthe most distressing cases the bank
OL,16,Fhandles due to their emotional and
OL,17,Ffinancial toll.
OL,19,F"Romance scams are some of the most
OL,20,Femotional situations that we support
OL,21,Fcustomers through," he said.
